				Im sorry I tend to disagree with alot of this mainly because I have found that if you are soloing (yeah right) all of this matters.  I have found how ever that if you are in a group and the group is well rounded you should not have any problems as far as stats and what have you.  If you look at class/race based issues you will never have the kind of experience that one should have in Norrath.  Of course I ahve never been told that I am not needed or wanted being a Paladin, and I ahve never had trouble within a group.  If I am in danger of dying, the Cleric saves me as is their job.  If I am tiring the druid zings me as part of their job.  But if I am alone I heal, zing, buff myself, what more could you want?  (Besides a Tele of that frozen rock)  The point is play a class because you enjoy it, and if you play for PHAT L33WTZ and all that other crap, find an uber guidl that will take you after you reach lvl 50.  But while you are trying to make lvl 50 you better make sure you have lots of friends that play the game the same way, and not like I do......to have fun and enjoy the world we have created.  I have enjoyed my Paladin and will continue to do so.  Again it is all in the make up of your character and how YOU choose to play, for PHAT L33WT read the above text, to have fun and discover what there is to know create a Paladin and jump in.<BR>
